# wrangler-only local vars for `wrangler dev --config wrangler.queue.jsonc`
# (src/worker/, the Cloudflare Worker consumer). Copy this file to
# `.dev.vars` — NOT `.env`, which is read by the SvelteKit app, not by
# wrangler. `.dev.vars` is gitignored and is never read by `wrangler
# deploy`, so this can never leak into a real deployment.
#
# Enables src/worker/index.ts's fetch() handler, which lets the SvelteKit
# app's producer (src/lib/server/queue.ts) push jobs into this Worker's
# locally-simulated "hello" queue over plain HTTP instead of Cloudflare's
# real API — no Cloudflare account needed for local dev. Pair with
# QUEUE_LOCAL_PUSH_URL in the app's own .env (see .env.example).
LOCAL_DEV_PUSH_ENABLED=true
